cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.CV, cs.SY

This paper is primarily focused on machine learning and distributed computing, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-categories. The use of large datasets and neural networks also suggests that it could belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The use of Imagenet and resnet50 in the experiments suggests that it could belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. Finally, the mention of adversaries and fault tolerance suggests that it could belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category.
